    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4496875>
    dc:description "FIGURE 31. Phyllodoce tupana sp. nov. A, anterior end in dorso-lateral view in a preserved specimen; B, distal part of proboscis showing terminal ring with papillae; C, inset showing micropapillae in the terminal ring; D, living specimen in dorsal view with extended proboscis. A–C, Holotype; E, proboscis with eggs. Scale bars: A, 2.0 mm; B, 0.1 mm; C–E, 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4496875/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4496877>
    dc:description "FIGURE 32. Phyllodoce tupana sp. nov. Anterior view of parapodia. A, parapodium 5 with eggs; B, holotype parapodium 25 with eggs; C, parapodium 75; D, parapodium 170 with eggs. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.6 mm; C, 1.0 mm; D, 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4496877/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4496879>
    dc:description "FIGURE 33. Phyllodoce tupana sp. nov. A, a parapodium showing asymmetry of lobes; B, detail of a compound spinigerous chaeta from a supracicular lobe; C, pygidium with two pairs of anal cirri; D, pygidium of a paratype with one pair of anal cirri. A–C, Holotype. Scale bars: A, 0.01 mm; B, 0.005 mm; C, 0.05 mm; D, 0.04 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4496879/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

